pageContext.claim: “In some cases like South Korea you know they're making a fortune. Well we backed them many years ago... Now we have a very big trade deficit with them, and we protect them. So we lose money on trade, and we lose money on the military. ”
pageContext.analysis: South Korea is the U.S.'s sixth biggest trading partner. In 2016, the U.S. has an overall trade deficit of $17 billion with South Korea, a number that is much smaller than the deficits with other trading partners.
